('SAT', 'Which choice most effectively uses data from the table to support Dr. Morales''s claim that greater weekly volunteer time is associated with higher vegetable harvest?', 'Dr. Morales studied community garden plots over one growing season, with cultivation methods held constant. Dr. Morales hypothesized that groups with greater weekly volunteer time would show higher vegetable harvest.

The table summarizes the results.

| Weekly volunteer time (hours) | Vegetable harvest (lbs) |
| --- | --- |
| 9 | 415 |
| 15 | 525 |
| 21 | 635 |
| 27 | 745 |', 'passage', 'multiple_choice', '[{"id":"A","text":"At 15 hours of weekly volunteer time, vegetable harvest measured 525 lbs.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Incorrect (too narrow). One row by itself cannot show a trend across the table."},{"id":"B","text":"As weekly volunteer time rose from 9 to 27 hours, vegetable harvest increased from 415 to 745 lbs.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct. It cites the endpoints and reports vegetable harvest rising as weekly volunteer time rises — the direct support the claim needs."},{"id":"C","text":"As weekly volunteer time rose from 9 to 27 hours, vegetable harvest fell from 745 to 415 lbs.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Incorrect (wrong direction). The table shows vegetable harvest rising, not falling, as weekly volunteer time increases."},{"id":"D","text":"The table lists four different levels of weekly volunteer time.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Incorrect (off-topic). Counting the rows says nothing about how vegetable harvest relates to weekly volunteer time."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Step 1 — Read the table. Each row pairs a weekly volunteer time level with the measured vegetable harvest.

Step 2 — Match the data to the claim. The correct choice cites the values that show vegetable harvest rising as weekly volunteer time rises across the range. Each distractor fails for a different reason — wrong direction, only the extremes, a single row, restating the claim without data, or treating association as proof of cause.', 'Information and Ideas', 'Command of Evidence', 'reading_writing', 'easy', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"rw_subtype":"quantitative_table","rw_format":"table_chart","generator":"generate-coe-fresh.mjs","coe_fresh_v1":true,"dsat_blueprint_v1":true,"length_tiered":true}'::jsonb, 'information', 'COE', false),
